5:
Garlic, ginger. Pumpkin and tomato. 
Chicken, too.
8: Perhaps I should make red stew.
13: Out of the way, out of the way!
27: Is it normal to see stars?
32:
I'm so sorry! Are you hurt? If only I had 
been looking forward then—
34:
Gah! But I'm in so much trouble! 
Awww, what in the skies do I do!
37:
She should still be in the market! After 
her!
42:
Eeek! You can't tell them you saw me, 
okay?!
45:
Strange. I could've sworn she went this 
way... Oh, Stella?
47:
Perfect timing! Did you happen to see 
a strange young woman run through 
here?
53:
Ah! Which way did she go?! She came 
out of the ground with a huge 
explosion—she's gotta be a monster!
54:
And probably one from the 
Kaleidoscope, if I had to bet my 
pension. We have to put 'er down 
before she blows up the place.
58:
She went through the market. I saw 
her exit on the other side.
61:
You did? Perfect! Thanks, Stella! You be 
careful, okay?
70: M-me? Look at my pretty face...
73:
How could I be a monster and look this 
cute? I'm Clarisse, journeyman 
alchemist! Yay!
81:
Clarisse, did you cause this massive 
hole?
84:
Yes, b-but! I was just practicing with 
Master when I got a spell wrong and 
suddenly I was in this weird maze 
thingy!
90:
Then these monsters came out of 
nowhere, and Master wasn't there to 
fight them! And I couldn't use my 
alchemy!
95:
But then my instincts took over my 
powers, and when that happens, well—
98: KAPOW! My magic kinda bursts out.
104:
The explosion... Is this what alchemy 
does?
107:
Mm, kind of? That's all mine does, but 
I'm still working on it.
110:
Thus you used your power to create 
a shaft from the labyrinth... all the way 
to the surface?
117:
Yeah, you get it! If I could control my 
atomic dissolution, I think I could've 
been more delicate though.
119:
But—you know what they say—if you 
can't beat, blast 'em!
125:
I understand now why the guards were 
pursuing you.
128:
You do? That was so dumb, making 
me run first thing in the morning!
135:
And I haven't even had breakfast yet. 
Do you know any food around here, 
Stella?
138:
Hmm. Yes, I do. And today the flavors 
should be exceptional.
144:
It is very far. But we can arrive there in 
an instant.
150:
Wow! Look at that big marble float! Is 
that the World Flipper thing you 
mentioned, Stella?
153:
Wh-whoa... Wait a minute. I've really 
crossed into a different dimension.
161:
She is an alchemist by the name of 
Clarisse.
168:
That makes sense. Explains why 
I couldn't use my alchemy at first.
171:
But I can get by without my atomic 
dissolution, especially if I put my mind 
to it.
174:
No! What am I saying! I'm on a whole 
'nother WORLD! Gaaah! I'm gonna die!
182:
Hey now! Of course I'm being dramatic
—I don't know anything about this 
place!
184:
All I can do is follow my own path, on 
my own time, and just hope it works 
out for the best! Yep!
188:
Would you like to intersect paths with 
us?
195:
We're already searching for a certain 
world. We could look for yours along 
the way.
199:
A-are you sure? People tell me I can be 
kind of annoying?
203:
Of course. Welcome to Starview 
Village. You have a home here now, 
Clarisse.
207:
Aww, thanks, you guys! We're going to 
be best friends!
210:
My crew... Master... You're all going to 
have to wait for me. But I'll make it 
home! For sure!
